The ABC islands are the three western-most islands of the Leeward Antilles in the Caribbean Sea that lie north of Falcón State , Venezuela .
From west to east they are , in order Aruba , Curaçao , and Bonaire .
All three islands are part of the Kingdom of the Netherlands , although they remain outside the European Union .
Aruba and Curaçao are autonomous , self-governing constituent countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands , while Bonaire is a special municipality of the Netherlands proper .